Package: dynamic_multiplex
Title: Community detection for identifying communities in evolving networked systems
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Jared",
           family = "Edgerton",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "jared.edgerton@gmail.com")
Description: Two-stage temporal community detection with customizable interlayer ties. Stage 1 runs Louvain or Leiden community detection independently on each network layer. Stage 2 constructs post-hoc interlayer ties between detected communities using Jaccard similarity, overlap coefficient, node-strength weighted variants, or direct node identity links. Interlayer ties describe cross-layer relationships but do not influence per-layer community assignments. Supports user-specified layer connectivity via the layer_links argument, defaulting to adjacent-only temporal links that avoid the long-range pooling problem in standard multislice approaches.
